{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S9FKWppcjF56L1RoJMZWb6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report of the changes to the \"cloche list\" command implementation.\n\n## Summary of \"cloche list\" Command Implementation Changes\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the modified files, here's the complete understanding of the changes to the \"cloche list\" command:\n\n### 1. **Proto File Changes** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`)\n   - **ListRunsRequest** now includes a `project_dir` field (line 92):\n     ```protobuf\n     message ListRunsRequest {\n       bool all = 1;\n       string project_dir = 2;\n     }\n     ```\n   - **RunSummary** now includes a `project_dir` field (line 108):\n     ```protobuf\n     message RunSummary {\n       ...\n       string project_dir = 9;\n     }\n     ```\n   - Removed `OrchestrateRequest` and `OrchestrateResponse` messages entirely\n   - Added `follow` field to `StreamLogsRequest` for tail-like streaming\n\n### 2. **Generated Protobuf Files** (`/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go` and `cloche_grpc.pb.go`)\n   - Auto-generated code updated to reflect proto changes\n   - Message type indices adjusted (from 22 to 20 message types total)\n   - Added getter methods for new `ProjectDir` fields\n\n### 3. **CLI Implementation** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`)\n\n   **Updated usage message** (line 104):\n   ```\n   list [--all]                                List runs for current project (--all for all projects)\n   ```\n\n   **cmdList function logic** (lines 217-271):\n   - **Default behavior (no --all flag)**: \n     - Gets current working directory via `os.Getwd()`\n     - Sets `req.ProjectDir = cwd` to filter runs to current project\n     - No time limit when filtering by project\n   \n   - **--all flag behavior**:\n     - Sets `req.All = true` \n     - Shows all runs across all projects with no time limit\n   \n   - **Display formatting** (lines 246-270):\n     - Shows run ID, workflow name, state, and run type (host/container)\n     - Optionally displays title, container ID, and error message with truncation\n\n### 4. **Server Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n\n   **ListRuns RPC handler** (lines 387-417):\n   - Three-tier filtering logic:\n     1. If `req.ProjectDir != \"\"`: calls `s.store.ListRunsByProject(ctx, req.ProjectDir, time.Time{})` (no time filter)\n     2. Else if `req.All`: calls `s.store.ListRuns(ctx, time.Time{})` (all runs, no time limit)\n     3. Else: calls `s.store.ListRuns(ctx, time.Now().Add(-1*time.Hour))` (last hour)\n   \n   - Converts domain.Run objects to pb.RunSummary protobuf messages\n   - Includes `ProjectDir` field in response (line 413)\n\n### 5. **Storage Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`)\n\n   **RunStore interface** includes two methods:\n   - `ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)` (line 15)\n   - `ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)` (line 16)\n\n### 6. **SQLite Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n\n   **ListRunsByProject method** (lines 224-241):\n   ```go\n   func (s *Store) ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error) {\n     var rows *sql.Rows\n     var err error\n     if since.IsZero() {\n       rows, err = s.db.QueryContext(ctx,\n         `SELECT ...FROM runs WHERE project_dir = ? ORDER BY CASE WHEN state = 'running' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END, started_at DESC`,\n         projectDir)\n     } else {\n       rows, err = s.db.QueryContext(ctx,\n         `SELECT ...FROM runs WHERE project_dir = ? AND started_at >= ? ORDER BY CASE WHEN state = 'running' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END, started_at DESC`,\n         projectDir, formatTime(since))\n     }\n   ```\n   - Filters by `project_dir` column\n   - Supports optional time filtering\n   - Orders running runs first, then by started_at descending\n\n### 7. **Domain Model** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`)\n\n   **Run struct** includes `ProjectDir` field (line 39):\n   ```go\n   type Run struct {\n     ID             string\n     WorkflowName   string\n     State          RunState\n     // ... other fields ...\n     ProjectDir     string  // ← NEW FIELD\n     // ... more fields ...\n   }\n   ```\n\n### 8. **Tests** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`)\n\n   **New test: TestServer_ListRuns_FilterByProject** (lines 37-73):\n   - Creates two runs with different project directories\n   - Verifies project filtering works correctly\n   - Verifies `--all` flag returns both runs\n   - Tests that `ProjectDir` field is properly populated in response\n\n### Key Behavior Changes\n\n| Scenario | Before | After |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| `cloche list` (no args) | Shows all runs from last hour | Shows only runs from current project (no time limit) |\n| `cloche list --all` | Shows all runs from all projects (last hour) | Shows all runs from all projects (no time limit) |\n| Run filtering scope | Time-based only | Time-based OR project-based |\n| ProjectDir in response | Not included | Included in RunSummary |\n\nAll modified files are located at:\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go`\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4be456c013d9c263 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51929\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 27664</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b681cdd1-b2f2-4224-b489-8b848ed1cf19","uuid":"95afec0e-5adb-4bde-8f33-62eef3ae97e5","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the current source code to understand the \"cloche list\" command implementation, particularly:\n1. Read the git diff for all modified files (run `git diff` and `git diff --cached`)\n2. Find the cloche list command implementation - look in cmd/cloche/ for list-related code\n3. Look for any --all flag or project filtering logic\n4. Check internal/adapters/grpc/server.go and server_test.go for list-related changes\n5. Check the proto file api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto for ListRuns or similar RPCs\n6. Read the generated pb files for list-related messages\n\nBe thorough - read the full content of changed files.","agentId":"a4be456c013d9c263","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report of the changes to the \"cloche list\" command implementation.\n\n## Summary of \"cloche list\" Command Implementation Changes\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the modified files, here's the complete understanding of the changes to the \"cloche list\" command:\n\n### 1. **Proto File Changes** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`)\n   - **ListRunsRequest** now includes a `project_dir` field (line 92):\n     ```protobuf\n     message ListRunsRequest {\n       bool all = 1;\n       string project_dir = 2;\n     }\n     ```\n   - **RunSummary** now includes a `project_dir` field (line 108):\n     ```protobuf\n     message RunSummary {\n       ...\n       string project_dir = 9;\n     }\n     ```\n   - Removed `OrchestrateRequest` and `OrchestrateResponse` messages entirely\n   - Added `follow` field to `StreamLogsRequest` for tail-like streaming\n\n### 2. **Generated Protobuf Files** (`/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go` and `cloche_grpc.pb.go`)\n   - Auto-generated code updated to reflect proto changes\n   - Message type indices adjusted (from 22 to 20 message types total)\n   - Added getter methods for new `ProjectDir` fields\n\n### 3. **CLI Implementation** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`)\n\n   **Updated usage message** (line 104):\n   ```\n   list [--all]                                List runs for current project (--all for all projects)\n   ```\n\n   **cmdList function logic** (lines 217-271):\n   - **Default behavior (no --all flag)**: \n     - Gets current working directory via `os.Getwd()`\n     - Sets `req.ProjectDir = cwd` to filter runs to current project\n     - No time limit when filtering by project\n   \n   - **--all flag behavior**:\n     - Sets `req.All = true` \n     - Shows all runs across all projects with no time limit\n   \n   - **Display formatting** (lines 246-270):\n     - Shows run ID, workflow name, state, and run type (host/container)\n     - Optionally displays title, container ID, and error message with truncation\n\n### 4. **Server Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n\n   **ListRuns RPC handler** (lines 387-417):\n   - Three-tier filtering logic:\n     1. If `req.ProjectDir != \"\"`: calls `s.store.ListRunsByProject(ctx, req.ProjectDir, time.Time{})` (no time filter)\n     2. Else if `req.All`: calls `s.store.ListRuns(ctx, time.Time{})` (all runs, no time limit)\n     3. Else: calls `s.store.ListRuns(ctx, time.Now().Add(-1*time.Hour))` (last hour)\n   \n   - Converts domain.Run objects to pb.RunSummary protobuf messages\n   - Includes `ProjectDir` field in response (line 413)\n\n### 5. **Storage Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`)\n\n   **RunStore interface** includes two methods:\n   - `ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)` (line 15)\n   - `ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)` (line 16)\n\n### 6. **SQLite Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n\n   **ListRunsByProject method** (lines 224-241):\n   ```go\n   func (s *Store) ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error) {\n     var rows *sql.Rows\n     var err error\n     if since.IsZero() {\n       rows, err = s.db.QueryContext(ctx,\n         `SELECT ...FROM runs WHERE project_dir = ? ORDER BY CASE WHEN state = 'running' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END, started_at DESC`,\n         projectDir)\n     } else {\n       rows, err = s.db.QueryContext(ctx,\n         `SELECT ...FROM runs WHERE project_dir = ? AND started_at >= ? ORDER BY CASE WHEN state = 'running' THEN 0 ELSE 1 END, started_at DESC`,\n         projectDir, formatTime(since))\n     }\n   ```\n   - Filters by `project_dir` column\n   - Supports optional time filtering\n   - Orders running runs first, then by started_at descending\n\n### 7. **Domain Model** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`)\n\n   **Run struct** includes `ProjectDir` field (line 39):\n   ```go\n   type Run struct {\n     ID             string\n     WorkflowName   string\n     State          RunState\n     // ... other fields ...\n     ProjectDir     string  // ← NEW FIELD\n     // ... more fields ...\n   }\n   ```\n\n### 8. **Tests** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`)\n\n   **New test: TestServer_ListRuns_FilterByProject** (lines 37-73):\n   - Creates two runs with different project directories\n   - Verifies project filtering works correctly\n   - Verifies `--all` flag returns both runs\n   - Tests that `ProjectDir` field is properly populated in response\n\n### Key Behavior Changes\n\n| Scenario | Before | After |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| `cloche list` (no args) | Shows all runs from last hour | Shows only runs from current project (no time limit) |\n| `cloche list --all` | Shows all runs from all projects (last hour) | Shows all runs from all projects (no time limit) |\n| Run filtering scope | Time-based only | Time-based OR project-based |\n| ProjectDir in response | Not included | Included in RunSummary |\n\nAll modified files are located at:\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go`\n- `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche_grpc.pb.go`\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`"}],"totalDurationMs":27664,"totalTokens":51929,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1010,"cache_read_input_tokens":49262,"output_tokens":1654,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1010},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
